ys/ashhurst-durham-street-reserve-mccraes-bush/ |archivedate=2015-01-14 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ashhurst.org/ashhurst/parks/|title=ashhurst dot org :: Parks|publisher=|accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wikimapia.org/27767550/McCrae-s-Bush|title=McCrae's Bush - Wikimapia|publisher=|accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n* Lincoln Park - The home ground to the local rugby team Ashhurst-[[Pohangina]] RFC\n\n==History==\nAshhurst was named for ''Lord Henry Ashhurst'', who owned land in the immediate area. The [[M\u0101ori language|M\u0101ori]] name for the area is [[Pseudopanax|Raukawa]], after a native aromatic plant (''Pseudopanax edgerleyi''), whereas for the town it is Otangaki.<ref name=lordashhurst>{{cite book | first=A. W. | last=Reed | title=The Reed Dictionary of New Zealand Place Names | publisher=Reed Books | location=Auckland | year=2002 | isbn=0-7900-0761-4}}</ref>\n\n==Local and central government representation==\n\n===Former Ashhurst-Fitzherbert Ward===\nAshhurst-Fitzherbert Ward is Palmerston North's largest ward covering the area from James Line to part way through the Manawatu Gorge, to just north of Ashhurst township. Recently [[Fitzherbert]] Ward was amalgamated with Ashhurst Ward.\n\nThe ward is predominantly rural, with most of the population living in Ashhurst, Aokautere and Linton. The area varies from the suburban to the foothills of the [[Tararua Ranges]] to the river valleys of the Manawatu and Pohangina Rivers.\n\nThe Saddle Road Bridge, which crosses this river, had to be recently replaced due to floods in 2004 when a flooded [[Pohangina River]] swept the bridge away.\nSaddle Road is the alternative route east when the [[Manawatu Gorge]] is closed.\n\nThere is an increasing amount of development in the area especially around [[Aokautere]] and Summerhill.{{fact|date=December 2017}}\n\nBecause of the higher ground on the south bank of the Manawatu, there are views of the [[Ruahine Ranges]] and the northern parts of the city. On a clear day it is possible to see [[Mount Ruapehu|Ruapehu]], [[Ngauruhoe]] and [[Mount Taranaki|Taranaki]].\n\n{| class=\"infobox bordered\" align=left cellpadding=4 cellspacing=0 width=275 style=\"clear:right; margin: 0 0 1em 1em; background: #f9f9f9;  font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n|colspan=3 align=center bgcolor=\"#f9f9f9\"|<big>Wards of Palmerston North</big>\n|-\n! Ward Name !! Suburbs including !! Councillor(s)\n|-\n|'''Ashhurst-Fitzherbert Ward''' || Aokautere, Ashhurst, Linton, Whakarongo, Turitea || ''Two'' - Cr. Duncan McCann,\n[http://www.pncc.govt.nz/Council/TheCouncil/MayorAndCouncillors.htm?searchstring=&pos=&sel=2&ID=35#35] \n|}\n\n===Central government===\n\n* [[Rangit\u012bkei (New Zealand electorate)|Rangit\u012bkei]] is represented by [[New Zealand National Party]] MP [[Ian McKelvie]].\n* [[Te Tai Hau\u0101uru]] is represented by [[New Zealand Labour Party]] MP [[Adrian Rurawhe]].\n\n==Education==\n\nAshhurst School is a co-educational state primary school for Year 1 to 8 students,<ref name=\"official2337\">{{cite web |title=Ashhurst School Official School Website |url=http://www.ashhurst.school.nz |website=ashhurst.school.nz}}</ref><ref name=\"moe2337\">{{cite web |title=Ashhurst School Ministry of Education School Profile |url=https://www.educationcounts.govt.nz/find-school/school/profile?school=2337 |website=educationcounts.govt.nz |publisher=[[Ministry of Education (New Zealand)|Ministry of Education]]}}</ref> with a roll of {{NZ school roll data|2337|y}} as of {{NZ school roll data|||y|}}.<ref name=\"ero2337\">{{cite web |title=Ashhurst School Education Review Office Report |url=http://www.ero.govt.nz/report-view?id=2337 |website=ero.govt.nz |publisher=[[Education Review Office]]}}</ref>\n\nHiwinui School, located north-west of the Ashhurst township, is also a co-educational state primary school for Year 1 to 8 students, located north-west of the township.<ref name=\"moe2364 \">{{cite web |title=Hiwinui School Ministry of Education School Profile |url=https://www.educationcounts.govt.nz/find-school/school/profile?school=2364 |website=educationcounts.govt.nz |publisher=[[Ministry of Education (New Zealand)|Ministry of Education]]}}</ref> It has a roll of {{NZ school roll data|2364|y}}.<ref name=\"ero2364 \">{{cite web |title=Hiwinui School Education Review Office Report |url=http://www.ero.govt.nz/report-view?id=2364 |website=ero.govt.nz |publisher=[[Education Review Office]]}}</ref>\n\n==Notable people==\n\n*[[Andre Taylor]], rugby player\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* https://web.archive.org/web/20050418224210/http://www.ashhurstnz.com/\n\n{{Palmerston North City}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Manawat\u016b-Whanganui]]\n[[Category:Suburbs of Palmerston North]]\n", "name_user": "Schwede66", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript, date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashhurst"}
